.TH graduat 2 "Novembre 1993" "Scilab Group" "Scilab Function" 
.so man1/sci.an
.SH NAME
graduat - pretty axis graduations
.SH CALLING SEQUENCE
.nf
[xi,xa,np]=graduat( xmi, xma,n1,n2)	
[xi,xa,np]=graduat( xmi, xma)
.fi
.SH PARAMETERS 
.TP 10
xmi,xma
: real scalars
.TP 
n1, n2
: integers with default values 3,10
.TP
xi, xa
:real scalars
.TP
np
: integer
.SH DESCRIPTION
graduat looks for the mimimum interval \fV[xi,xa]\fR and a number of tics 
\fVnp\fR such that:
.LP
\fVxi <= xmi <= xma <= xa\fR
.LP
\fVxa - xi / np  =  k(10^n)\fR,\fVk\fR in \fV[1 3 5]\fR  for an integer \fVn\fR
.LP
\fVn1 < np < n2\fR
.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
  y=(0:0.33:145.78)';
  xbasc();plot2d1('enn',0,y)
  [ymn,ymx,np]=graduat(mini(y),maxi(y))
  rect=[1,ymn,prod(size(y)),ymx];
  xbasc();plot2d1('enn',0,y,-1,'011',' ',rect,[10,3,10,np])
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
xsetech ,plot2d
